Description:
State Window Corporation, Awarded Canada's Best Managed Company of 2021, is a PROFIT 500 manufacturing and construction company located in Vaughan, ON. Together, we manufacture, design and install window wall, curtain wall and railing systems for high rise condominiums. We are looking for individuals who are interested in thriving professionally at a rapidly growing company with an inclusive and engaging culture. A career at State Window Corporation means you can become a part of a clear purpose: one that brings change, innovation, and quality to city skylines, one project at a time.
Our team of talented and determined individuals, are endlessly driven by passion, dependability, honesty, and loyalty. We take pride in our work, people, and dedication to quality, every step of the way. Apply today if you are qualified applicant looking for a challenging and rewarding career!
NOW HIRING GENERAL LABOURS!
Full-time permanent, morning & afternoon shifts.
44 hrs per week
$16.50/hr+, $1.25 shift prem. + benefits.
Walk-ins welcomed Monday-Friday.
PH:
416-646-1421 x 203
, hr@statewindowcorp.com
220 Hunter’s Valley Rd, Vaughan, ON L4H 3V9
State is hiring full-time, permanent General Labourers, either on the Day Shift or Afternoon Shift, in all our divisions, (window wall, curtain wall, and railing).
Duties and Responsibilities:
General labour and/or fabrication duties of aluminum/glass products (windows, frames, glass);
Assemble parts or component parts;
Using silicone gun to glue window into frame;
Machine operation when required;
Must pay attention to details and make sure customer’s glasses are handled carefully;
Always follow safe working procedures;
Any other duties assigned by the Production Supervisor.
Qualifications Required
High School diploma or equivalent;
Basic knowledge of the tape measure, work tools/ screw gun, drill gun is an asset.
Experience in a manufacturing environment or glass window wall industry is an asset;
Knowledge of window wall or other window systems;
Hand eye coordination;
Regular attendance is critical;
Ability to use hand tools and accurately use a tape measure as required;
Positive working attitude;
Strong attention to detail and organizational skills;
Work in a team environment by demonstrating State’s core values (i.e. dependability, passion, honestly, and loyalty);
Good communication skills with the ability to take direction; and
Ability to work in a fast-paced environment.
Physical Demands and Abilities
Frequently lift up to 50 pounds and adjust body position to bend, stoop, stand, walk, turn, pivot, and stand for long periods of time;
Repetitive motion with hands and arms; and
Standing, twisting head, neck and upper body for entire shift.
Working Conditions
Factory manufacturing plant environment;
Work may involve some exposure to unusual elements, and loud noises;
Work environment involved some exposure to hazards of physical risks that require knowledge of an adherence to basic safety procedures; and
Work environment requires wearing PPE: safety footwear, safety glasses, hearing protection and a mask/face shield.
Hours of Operation:
44 hours per week
Day Shift
Monday – Thursday 6:30 a.m. – 4:00 p.m.
Friday 6:30 a.m. – 3:00 p.m.
Or
Afternoon Shift
Monday – Thursday 4:30 p.m. – 2:00 a.m.
Friday 3:30 p.m. – 12:00 a.m.
